  "bio_raw": "Dr. Rezwan Al Islam Khan is an accomplished academic and researcher specializing in robotics, embedded systems, and multi-agent control. With a Doctorate in Circuits and Systems from Fudan University, Shanghai, China, his expertise spans hybrid locomotion of bio-inspired robots, reinforcement learning, and control systems. Dr. Khan has a rich history of academic contributions, including publications in journals and conferences showcasing his innovative approaches to robotics and optimization. Currently serving as an Associate Professor at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB), he has held various academic roles, including at BUBT, Southeast University, and IUB. A recipient of numerous accolades, including the Chancellor's Gold Medal, Dr. Khan brings a blend of research insight and pedagogical excellence.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Robotics",
    "Embedded Systems",
    "Optimization",
    "Reinforcement Learning",
    "Multi-agent control",
    "Control Systems"
  ],
